sentences: Yekaterina Chemberdzhi (Russian: Екатерина Владимировна Чемберджи́), also Katia Tchemberdji (nickname) or Jekaterina Wladimirowna Tschemberdschi (German form) (born 6 May 1960), is a Russian pianist and composer.
In 1978 she studied composition and piano at the Moscow Conservatory with Nikolai Korndorf and Yuri Kholopov.
After ending her studies, Chemberdzhi took a position from 1984-90 teaching at the Moscow Gnessin State Musical College.
In 1990 she moved to West Berlin.
2003: Three Bow Dances, for cello and piano
2009: Die Fragen des Bartholomäus, for five solo singers, choir, organ and orchestra
